OL,7,F"A public inquiry would take years.
OL,8,FBut if there is a public inquiry ` if
OL,9,Fthat decision is made ` then we will
OL,10,Fwelcome it."
OL,12,F"There's no doubt about the need to
OL,13,Fget to the bottom of this problem and
OL,14,Fwe will leave no stone unturned to
OL,15,Ffind those answers."
OL,17,FFour councillors resigned from the
OL,18,Flocal authority's cabinet in the wake
OL,19,Fof the interview.
